:"mentions"},{"source":"recDBNQIuUdCDBm5t","target":"recWQDkxXj0IjAdkn","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"recJzXVQ4gA0WkIXu","ref":"Deut.3.1","text":"Then we turned, and went up the way to Bashan: and Og the king of Bashan came out against us, he and all his people, to battle at Edrei.","year":-1452},{"id":"recDXabilc7FSAn6H","ref":"Deut.3.2","text":"And the LORD said unto me, Fear him not: for I will deliver him, and all his people, and his land, into thy hand; and thou shalt do unto him as thou didst unto Sihon king of the Amorites, which dwelt at Heshbon.","year":-1452},{"id":"recgJ0L5QyuRqEB5W","ref":"Deut.3.3","text":"So the LORD our God delivered into our hands Og also, the king of Bashan, and all his people: and we smote him until none was left to him remaining.","year":-1452},{"id":"recixAySPy7tsHEiJ","ref":"Deut.3.4","text":"And we took all his cities at that time, there was not a city which we took not from them, threescore cities, all the region of Argob, the kingdom of Og in Bashan.","year":-1452},{"id":"recdHj6lkL2XNz69h","ref":"Deut.3.5","text":"All these cities were fenced with high walls, gates, and bars; beside unwalled towns a great many.","year":-1452},{"id":"recVNBDeUnU0xK3k6","ref":"Deut.3.6","text":"And we utterly destroyed them, as we did unto Sihon king of Heshbon, utterly destroying the men, women, and children, of every city.","year":-1452},{"id":"recff1dPQ9ay82uOl","ref":"Deut.3.7","text":"But all the cattle, and the spoil of the cities, we took for a prey to ourselves.","year":-1452},{"id":"rec6rAixINf4SLSeA","ref":"Deut.3.8","text":"And we took at that time out of the hand of the two kings of the Amorites the land that was on this side Jordan, from the river of Arnon unto mount Hermon;","year":-1452}]}
